{
    "level": "sentence",
    "abstract": [],
    "body_text": [
        {
            "text": "Recently the LHCb Collaboration [1] published the results of a search for the doubly charmed baryon \u039e + cc . ",
            "paragraph_rank": 2,
            "section_rank": 1,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 32,
                    "end": 35,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b0",
                    "text": "[1]"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "No significant signal is seen in the mass range from 3.4 to 3.8 GeV. ",
            "paragraph_rank": 2,
            "section_rank": 1
        },
        {
            "text": "To put this result in context, the \u039e ++ cc baryon was seen by LHCb in decay modes \u039b c K \u2212 \u03c0 + \u03c0 + [2] (2017) and \u039e + c \u03c0 + [3] (2018). ",
            "paragraph_rank": 2,
            "section_rank": 1,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 98,
                    "end": 101,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b1",
                    "text": "[2]"
                },
                {
                    "start": 123,
                    "end": 126,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b2",
                    "text": "[3]"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "The weighted average of the \u039e ++ cc mass is 3621.24 \u00b1 0.65 (stat.) \u00b1 0.31 (syst.) MeV [3].",
            "paragraph_rank": 2,
            "section_rank": 1,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 86,
                    "end": 89,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b2",
                    "text": "[3]"
                }
            ],
            "entity_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 82,
                    "end": 85,
                    "type": "software",
                    "rawForm": "MeV",
                    "resp": "whitelist",
                    "id": "software-simple-w0"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "The \u039e ++ cc and \u039e + cc have the quark content ccu and ccd, respectively. ",
            "paragraph_rank": 3,
            "section_rank": 1
        },
        {
            "text": "Under the isospin symmetry of the strong interactions they form an isodoublet, like the proton and the neutron. ",
            "paragraph_rank": 3,
            "section_rank": 1
        },
        {
            "text": "Isospin breaking in hadron masses is a very small effect [4]. ",
            "paragraph_rank": 3,
            "section_rank": 1,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 57,
                    "end": 60,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b3",
                    "text": "[4]"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "Consequently we have firm reasons to expect that the \u039e ++ cc \u2212 \u039e + cc mass difference is quite small, O(1.5) MeV [5]. ",
            "paragraph_rank": 3,
            "section_rank": 1,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 113,
                    "end": 116,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b4",
                    "text": "[5]"
                }
            ],
            "entity_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 109,
                    "end": 112,
                    "type": "software",
                    "rawForm": "MeV",
                    "resp": "whitelist",
                    "id": "software-simple-w1"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "The production rates of \u039e ++ cc and \u039e + cc should be similar, as the bottleneck-the production of the cc diquark-is the same in both cases. ",
            "paragraph_rank": 3,
            "section_rank": 1
        },
        {
            "text": "Consequently we know \u039e + cc exists in the vicinity of 3620 MeV. ",
            "paragraph_rank": 3,
            "section_rank": 1,
            "entity_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 59,
                    "end": 62,
                    "type": "software",
                    "rawForm": "MeV",
                    "resp": "whitelist",
                    "id": "software-simple-w2"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "A claimed \u039e + cc at (3518.7\u00b11.7) MeV [6,7] is unlikely to be the isospin partner of the established \u039e ++ cc , and has not been confirmed by any other experiment. ",
            "paragraph_rank": 3,
            "section_rank": 1,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 37,
                    "end": 40,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b5",
                    "text": "[6,"
                },
                {
                    "start": 40,
                    "end": 42,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b6",
                    "text": "7]"
                }
            ],
            "entity_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 33,
                    "end": 36,
                    "type": "software",
                    "rawForm": "MeV",
                    "resp": "whitelist",
                    "id": "software-simple-w3"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "The search was a \"blind analysis\", i.e., it was performed with the whole procedure defined before inspecting the data in the 3400 to 3800 MeV mass range. ",
            "paragraph_rank": 3,
            "section_rank": 1,
            "entity_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 138,
                    "end": 141,
                    "type": "software",
                    "rawForm": "MeV",
                    "resp": "whitelist",
                    "id": "software-simple-w4"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "A search for a \u039e + cc signal was performed and the significance of the signal as a function of the \u039e + cc mass was evaluated. ",
            "paragraph_rank": 3,
            "section_rank": 1
        },
        {
            "text": "If the global significance, after considering the look-elsewhere effect, was found to be above 3\u03c3, the \u039e + cc mass was measured; otherwise, up- per limits were set on the production rates for different CM energies.",
            "paragraph_rank": 3,
            "section_rank": 1
        },
        {
            "text": "As can be seen from Figure 2 in ref. ",
            "paragraph_rank": 4,
            "section_rank": 1,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 20,
                    "end": 28,
                    "type": "figure",
                    "text": "Figure 2"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "[1], the data exhibit several peaks, but the most significant one occurs just where it is expected. ",
            "paragraph_rank": 4,
            "section_rank": 1,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 0,
                    "end": 3,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b0",
                    "text": "[1]"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "The largest local significance, corresponding to 3.1\u03c3 (2.7\u03c3 after considering systematic uncertainties), occurs around 3620 MeV. ",
            "paragraph_rank": 4,
            "section_rank": 1,
            "entity_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 124,
                    "end": 127,
                    "type": "software",
                    "rawForm": "MeV",
                    "resp": "whitelist",
                    "id": "software-simple-w5"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "However, the look-elsewhere effect [8], intrinsic to the LHCb search procedure, reduces this to 1.7\u03c3. ",
            "paragraph_rank": 4,
            "section_rank": 1,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 35,
                    "end": 38,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b7",
                    "text": "[8]"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "We believe that in this case the look-elsewhere effect may be overstated, because the peak shows up nearly (but not precisely) where expected. ",
            "paragraph_rank": 4,
            "section_rank": 1
        },
        {
            "text": "The result of a fit, as given in the Supplementary Material of ref. ",
            "paragraph_rank": 4,
            "section_rank": 1
        },
        {
            "text": "[1], is M(\u039e + cc ) = (3623.4\u00b1 1.7) MeV, a bit larger than M(\u039e ++ cc ), in contrast to the prediction of ref. ",
            "paragraph_rank": 4,
            "section_rank": 1,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 0,
                    "end": 3,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b0",
                    "text": "[1]"
                }
            ],
            "entity_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 35,
                    "end": 38,
                    "type": "software",
                    "rawForm": "MeV",
                    "resp": "whitelist",
                    "id": "software-simple-w6"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "[5] and nearly all the others quoted there which find M(\u039e + cc ) less than but within a few MeV of M(\u039e ++ cc ). ",
            "paragraph_rank": 4,
            "section_rank": 1,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 0,
                    "end": 3,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b4",
                    "text": "[5]"
                }
            ],
            "entity_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 92,
                    "end": 95,
                    "type": "software",
                    "rawForm": "MeV",
                    "resp": "whitelist",
                    "id": "software-simple-w7"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "The upper limit on \u039e + cc production (or the significance of a signal) increases with shorter assumed lifetime, as seen in Table 6 and Figure 6 of ref. ",
            "paragraph_rank": 4,
            "section_rank": 1,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 123,
                    "end": 130,
                    "type": "table",
                    "text": "Table 6"
                },
                {
                    "start": 135,
                    "end": 143,
                    "type": "figure",
                    "text": "Figure 6"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "[1]. ",
            "paragraph_rank": 4,
            "section_rank": 1,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 0,
                    "end": 3,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b0",
                    "text": "[1]"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "As a result of the internal cd \u2192 su process in the decay of \u039e + cc , its lifetime is several times shorter than that of \u039e ++ cc : for example, ref. ",
            "paragraph_rank": 4,
            "section_rank": 1
        },
        {
            "text": "[9] finds \u03c4(\u039e + cc ) = 53 fs, and \u03c4(\u039e ++ cc ) = 185 fs. ",
            "paragraph_rank": 4,
            "section_rank": 1,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 0,
                    "end": 3,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b8",
                    "text": "[9]"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "(The latter was measured by LHCb to be 256 +24 \u221222 \u00b1 14 fs [10].) ",
            "paragraph_rank": 4,
            "section_rank": 1,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 59,
                    "end": 63,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b9",
                    "text": "[10]"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "The validity of the prediction of M(\u039e ++ cc ) [9] and the signal of its isospin partner not far from its predicted mass [5] lend credence to an estimate of the mass of the cc\u016bd tetraquark using similar methods, which finds this state to have a mass of (3882\u00b112) MeV [11] and hence unstable with respect to strong decay. ",
            "paragraph_rank": 4,
            "section_rank": 1,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 46,
                    "end": 49,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b8",
                    "text": "[9]"
                },
                {
                    "start": 120,
                    "end": 123,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b4",
                    "text": "[5]"
                },
                {
                    "start": 266,
                    "end": 270,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b10",
                    "text": "[11]"
                }
            ],
            "entity_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 262,
                    "end": 265,
                    "type": "software",
                    "rawForm": "MeV",
                    "resp": "whitelist",
                    "id": "software-simple-w8"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "The cross section for cc\u016bd tetraquark production is expected [11] to be somewhat, but not much, smaller than the cross section for production of \u039e ++ cc and \u039e + cc baryons. ",
            "paragraph_rank": 4,
            "section_rank": 1,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 61,
                    "end": 65,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b10",
                    "text": "[11]"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "Thus the new LHCb results provide additional motivation for continuing the search for the cc\u016bd tetraquark. ",
            "paragraph_rank": 4,
            "section_rank": 1
        },
        {
            "text": "In summary, the data contain a 2.7\u03c3 hint of the \u039e + cc signal at a mass consistent with predictions based on the measured \u039e ++ cc mass and isospin symmetry. ",
            "paragraph_rank": 4,
            "section_rank": 1
        },
        {
            "text": "More data are needed to exclude the possibility that this is a statistical fluctuation.",
            "paragraph_rank": 4,
            "section_rank": 1
        }
    ]
}